kpi_info.title: period_duration (period_duration)
kpi_info.use: Duration of the measurement period in minutes.

kpi_info.title: utran_not_able_exec_ishho_rt (M1010C0)
kpi_info.use: Number of inter-system handover failures for RT due to UTRAN. --- The failure can occur, for example, due to the following reasons: relocation preparation procedure failure in the CN, or relocation resource allocation procedure failure in the target BSC. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: ue_not_able_exec_ishho_rt (M1010C1)
kpi_info.use: "Number of times when during inter-system handover for RT the source RNC has ordered the UE to use a configuration which the UE does not support. --- If the source RNC instructs the UE to use a configuration that it does not support, the UE will send a failure message to the source RNC. The handover procedure ends and the UE resumes normal operation as if no handover attempt had occurred." Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

kpi_info.title: is_com_mod_sta_not_pos_rt (M1010C2)

The measurement is enabled by the parameter GSMcauseUplinkQuality. Note: This counter doesn't have a formula and the default (SUM) was used.

UPDATED:When the Inter-system handover ends, i.e., when the source RNC receives RANAP: IU RELEASE COMMAND message with cause "successful relocation" from the CN. This counter is updated only when the trigger reason is forced ISHO due to normal priority block resource procedure for remaining UEs and for NRT.

kpi_info.title: LTE_NOT_FOUND_REDIR (M1010C237)
kpi_info.use: The number of times when no good enough carrier frequency was found for LTE redirection during measurements performed by the UE.UPDATED:When no carrier frequency was found for LTE redirection during measurements, and the LTE carrier measurement is stopped due to maximum number of measurement reports received.

kpi_info.title: LTE_REDIR_START_AFTER_MEAS (M1010C238)
kpi_info.use: The number of times when LTE redirection was started after finding good enough carrier frequency with measurements performed by the UE.UPDATED:When the LTE carrier measurement performed by the UE finds a carrier frequency with acceptable quality to perform redirection and the RNC initiates the redirection procedure.

kpi_info.title: DURATION_LTE_MEASUREMENT (M1010C239)
kpi_info.use: The total duration for LTE frequency band measurements in SRNC. The start time of the measurement is when the Measurement Control is sent to the UE. The stop trigger for the measurement is when the measurement session ends either to perform the redirection/handover or not because no suitable carrier is found or the call was released or dropped during the measurement. The counter is updated only for the main cell of the connection. UPDATED: When the LTE frequency band measurement session ends to either perform the handover/redirection or not because there is no suitable carrier found or the call was released/dropped during the measurement.

kpi_info.title: LTE_N_ISHO_CM_DCH_CCH (M1010C240)

UPDATED:When either a relocation preparation to LTE is started or the RNC handover control decides that no cell is good enough for handover after measuring with compressed mode. This counter is not updated if the call is released during the measurement, or the UE does not send measurement reports as expected.
